20:18.509 --> 20:19.250
Some of us,

20:20.194 --> 20:23.477
We need to rest in that fact, realize that he's near.

20:23.497 --> 20:27.181
Early in that chapter of Philippians four verse five, he says, I am near you.

20:27.401 --> 20:28.222
God is near you.

20:29.963 --> 20:32.666
Realize that he's near and he's working all things together for a good.

20:32.686 --> 20:38.832
So the first way, contemplation, that's getting quiet before the Lord taking deep breaths and just sitting there in silence, resting in him.

20:38.892 --> 20:42.956
Number two is meditation.

20:43.937 --> 20:44.598
Meditation.

20:45.999 --> 20:48.061
As you know, you and I, we can pray the Bible.

20:48.101 --> 20:49.202
We read the Bible.

20:49.698 --> 20:54.403
But did you know that you and I, we can whisper the Bible back to the Lord?

20:55.924 --> 20:57.926
There's something happens to my anxiety.

20:57.966 --> 21:03.372
There's something happens with my fear when I begin to remind God of what he said to me.

21:04.072 --> 21:07.776
Because really I'm not reminding him, I'm reminding me.

21:09.117 --> 21:15.564
Now, God says in Isaiah, right, 43, he says, put me in remembrance of my word, but he doesn't forget.

21:16.445 --> 21:17.746
