26:20.739 --> 26:21.720
Sometimes runners have them.

26:21.740 --> 26:26.226
They got this big straw that comes around the front to keep you hydrated.

26:26.658 --> 26:33.265
I was, we were all excited, filled all the kids, came all bags up, we've got our bottles of water, we're excited.

26:33.285 --> 26:35.908
All right, this is gonna be Lana's first hiking trip.

26:36.429 --> 26:39.172
This little thing she's carrying is about probably one pound.

26:41.234 --> 26:48.402
And we literally get probably like 100 feet from the car and she starts complaining.

26:48.423 --> 26:50.605
She's like, oh, dad, this is so heavy.

26:50.825 --> 26:52.787
This bag is so heavy.

26:52.928 --> 26:54.589
